Self-awareness is like having a mirror for your mind—it’s the ability to recognize and understand your own emotions, thoughts, and behaviors. It's what helps you realize why you react a certain way in situations, identify your strengths and weaknesses, and improve your interactions with others.

There are two main types of self-awareness:

Internal Self-Awareness – This is about understanding yourself, your values, and what drives you. It helps you make decisions that align with who you are.

External Self-Awareness – This is about knowing how others perceive you. It allows you to adjust your behavior and communication for better relationships.

The more self-aware you become, the better you can manage your emotions, set goals effectively, and make thoughtful choices. Have you ever had a moment where self-awareness changed the way you handled something?

Whereas The Company intends develop a lightweight business intelligence software tool that lets small business users (especially retail, Quick Service Restaurants (QSRs), and eCom, etc) upload their sales or customer data, then automatically generates clean dashboards plus simple written insights based on that data (hereinafter referred to as “THE PRODUCT”). The Company has disclosed, inter alia, the concept of the Product, and intends to disclose certain proprietary information to the Developer for the purpose of developing the Product. The Developer has warranted that he possesses the requisite skill set, technical expertise, and experience necessary to develop the Product. The Company desires to ensure that such information is kept confidential and not disclosed or used without its consent.  Confidential Information For the purposes of this Agreement, “Confidential Information” means all non-public, proprietary, or confidential information disclosed by the Company to the Developer, whether orally, visually, or in writing, including but not limited to the concept, idea, design, features, functionalities, architecture, workflow, technical specifications, source code, algorithms, documents, data, prototypes, business plans, pricing, customer information, and any other information relating to the Product or development process. Confidential Information includes the idea or concept of the Product itself, whether or not reduced to material form, and all discussions relating thereto.  Obligations of the Developer The Developer agrees to: keep the Confidential Information strictly confidential and not disclose it to any third party without the prior written consent of the Company; use the Confidential Information solely to develop the Product for the Company; take all reasonable steps to protect the Confidential Information from unauthorised disclosure or use; not reverse-engineer, replicate, or otherwise exploit the Confidential Information for personal or commercial benefit.  Non-Use and Non-Circumvention The Developer shall not develop, design, replicate, or assist any third party in developing or replicating, any software, system, or product based on the Confidential Information without the Company’s prior written approval. The Developer shall not circumvent or attempt to bypass the Company’s interest in the disclosed concept in any manner whatsoever.  Return or Destruction Upon the Company’s request, the Developer shall promptly return or destroy all materials containing Confidential Information, including all copies, notes, or reproductions.  Intellectual Property All intellectual property rights in the Confidential Information and any software or product that may result from its use shall belong solely to the Company. Nothing in this Agreement shall be construed as granting the Developer any rights, by licence or otherwise, to the Confidential Information.  Duration This Agreement shall remain in effect from the date of execution, and the obligations herein shall survive the termination or expiration of any business relationship between the parties.  Remedies The Developer acknowledges that unauthorised disclosure or use of the Confidential Information may cause irreparable harm to the Company for which monetary damages may be inadequate. Accordingly, the Company shall be entitled to seek injunctive relief and any other legal or equitable remedies available under law  Governing Law This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Federal Repubic of Nigeria.  DISPUTE RESOLUTION The Parties shall use their best endeavours to resolve any dispute or difference of opinion between them, arising from or in connection with this Agreement amicably through mutual discussion.  In the event that the Parties are unable to settle the dispute, difference or controversy amicably, such dispute shall, within thirty (30) days of the breakdown of the settlement, be referred to mediation. The mediation shall be conducted in English language in Nigeria and in accordance with the rules of mediation at the Oyo State Multi-Door Courthouse.  Entire Agreement This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties with respect to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior or contemporaneous understandings, whether oral or written.
